text:
A string of robberies since mid-September is the work of the same group of criminals, according to the Atlanta Police Department, which is seeking the public’s help in catching the suspects.
APD released images of the suspects, who have hit fast-food restaurants, gas stations and an auto parts store between Sept. 18 and Oct. 10. The robberies generally occurred between 8 p.m. and 12:30 a.m.
Several images show the suspects aiming handguns at store employees. One suspect has his face covered while another does not.
The Atlanta Police Department released a series of images of suspects in a string of robberies since mid-September. Information on the suspects can be submitted anonymously by calling the Crime Stoppers Atlanta tip line at 404-577-TIPS (8477), by visiting www.crimestoppersatlanta.org or by texting the tip to CSA at CRIMES (274637). A reward of up to $2,000 is being offered for the arrest and indictment of the suspects.
Police said they continue to gather information on the following robberies:
